subSubSection.paragraph:
Female ( IBSP 91252 ). Coloration as in male, except abdomen darker (
Fig. 4
). Total length 6.8 . Carapace 2.9 long, 2.1 wide. Clypeus 0.06 high. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.16 , ALE 0.16 , PME 0.18 , PLE 0.20 ; AME‒AME 0.06 , AME‒ALE 0.04 , PME‒PME 0.14 , PME‒PLE 0.10 , ALE‒PLE 0.06 . Chelicerae with 3 promarginal teeth and 8 retromarginal denticles. Femora lengths: I 2.4 ; II 2.4 ; III 2.1 ; IV 2.8 . Spination differs from male on leg I—tibia p 0-1 -0, r 0-1 -0, metatarsus p 0-1 -0, r 0-1 - 1 ; II—tibia p 1 - 1 -0, r 0-1 -0; III—metatarsus p 1 - 1 -0, r 1 - 1 -0; IV—tibia p 1 - 1 -0, r 1 - 1 -0. Epyginum internaly with oval spermathecae and long, coiled ducts (
Figs 15, 17, 18
).
